summary: Democratic Congresswoman Sheila Jackson Lee of Texas has passed away at the age of 74 after a battle with cancer. A longtime advocate for African Americans, Lee served in the U.S. House of Representatives for nearly three decades, representing Houston and its surrounding areas. President Biden expressed his condolences and praised Lee's dedication to her constituents and her unwavering commitment to social justice. Throughout her career, Lee was known for her assertive and outspoken nature, earning her the nickname "tough lady."

name: Ben Sasse
summary: University of Florida (UF) President Ben Sasse has recently announced his resignation from his position. The decision came after his wife's health condition, epilepsy, worsened. Former UF President Kent Fuchs is set to serve as interim president following Sasse's departure. Sasse expressed his gratitude for the opportunity to lead UF and his best wishes to the university and its community.
